# The amendment reaction (see the amendment-flow framing in PROJECT.md / AGENTS.md).
#
# Tianheng's constitution is the law. Changing the law is an *amendment* and requires
# steward review, so an agent cannot silently weaken a boundary to make CI pass. The
# review requirement is the reaction: a merge cannot relax the law without a human
# accepting it.
#
# The protected file must be the boundary whose edit turns CI green after drift, not a
# showcase of it:
#   - crates/tianheng/tests/self_governance.rs is Tianheng's SELF-GOVERNING constitution
#     — the boundaries it enforces on itself (the 圭表 core is serde_json-only; the core
#     crate must not depend on the gate/shell). It is the file an agent would weaken to
#     make Tianheng's own CI pass, so it is the primary thing to protect.
#   - deny.toml is the supply-chain gate backing the same dependency-light invariant;
#     weakening it likewise relaxes the law.
#   - crates/tianheng/src/constitution.rs is only the bundled DEMO constitution (target
#     `example-core`); protected so the adoption showcase cannot rot, but it gates
#     nothing on its own.
#
# Designation alone only auto-requests review. To make review *required* (block a merge
# that relaxes the law), the repo admin must enable branch protection on the default
# branch with "Require review from Code Owners". Until then this documents intent.

/crates/tianheng/tests/self_governance.rs   @tacticaldoll
/crates/tianheng/src/constitution.rs        @tacticaldoll
/deny.toml                                  @tacticaldoll
